  "description": "Found by me, Lorraine Lanning. I initially found the bird when I rounded the SE corner of the lake, perched on top of a willow. Followed it along the willows, up on a fence, then along the trail, taking phone photos for documentation. Stayed with the bird while I got the info out, then ran home for my camera, went back, other birders arrived, bird was refound.Foraging in and out of willows along trail mainly, eating grasshoppers. Another birder played the call & it responded. Not particularly skittish, frequently within feet of m.o.b.",
